{"parentUuid":"0785f5dc-990e-43e2-8959-399a9c25df6a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshQrp6tTPJRApJRKCze","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JzWbJc2bDEFUwxBPaWJb2X","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-report.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15768,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15768,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcshQqr4pF3PYs9JUkKyt","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"106023b4-bc61-41fc-86f6-c1c245e85fa6","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:51:43.308Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"106023b4-bc61-41fc-86f6-c1c245e85fa6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JzWbJc2bDEFUwxBPaWJb2X","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: clean\n3\tran_at: 2026-07-10T01:55:58Z\n4\tscope: diff\n5\tsince_commit: ef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4\n6\tcritical_count: 0\n7\twarning_count: 2\n8\tfixed_count: 1\n9\ttotal_findings: 3\n10\tsemgrep_findings: 0\n11\tosv_findings: 2\n12\tcheckov_findings: 0\n13\ttrivy_findings: 0\n14\tstride_mechanisms_verified: 10\n15\tstride_mechanisms_missing: 0\n16\tstride_new_threats: 0\n17\tasvs_reconciled: true\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t# Security report — quota administration (GET /v1/quotas list + DELETE /v1/quotas)\n21\t\n22\tBranch `feature/quota-admin`. Scope = diff against `HEAD` (ef3fb3f). **No critical findings.**\n23\tThe implementation is well-hardened: parameterized SQL, anchored allowlist validation, admin-scope\n24\tgate, per-tenant `api_key_id` filtering with FORCE RLS backstop, minimal response projection, and a\n25\tfail-closed generic-500 error boundary.\n26\t\n27\t## Tools run this pass\n28\t\n29\t| Tool | Scope | Result |\n30\t|---|---|---|\n31\t| Semgrep (auto + p/secrets + p/owasp-top-ten + p/python) | 7 changed code/test files | 0 findings, 0 errors |\n32\t| Gitleaks (dir) | full tree | 0 in change set (128 out-of-scope, see below) |\n33\t| OSV Scanner | poetry.lock | 1 CVE (2 alias ids), dev-only, below gate floor |\n34\t| Trivy fs (vuln,secret,misconfig) | src/ | 0 findings |\n35\t| lockfile-check | change set | clean (no manifest/lockfile drift) |\n36\t| asvs-sast (Tier-1 deterministic) | change set | 0 critical |\n37\t| ast-grep (structural, advisory) | changed src | clean (see 6d) |\n38\t| generate-sbom | project | wrote .pipeline/sbom.cdx.json, 65 components |\n39\t\n40\tCheckov not run: **no `infra/` `.tf` file changed** in this diff (the only untracked `infra/` entries\n41\twere the local `.terraform/` provider cache — see fix below). Trivy `config`/`image` not run: no\n42\tDockerfile or built image in the change set. Both legitimately omitted from `scan_artifacts`.\n43\t\n44\t## Change-set diff-scope\n45\t\n46\tTracked: `PROJECT.md`, `.gitignore` (fixed this pass), `src/api/middleware.py`,\n47\t`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`,\n48\t`src/services/quota_service.py`, `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py`. Untracked:\n49\t`tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py`, `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` (the provider lock —\n50\tlegitimately committable, kept).\n51\t\n52\t## Complete findings inventory\n53\t\n54\t| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n55\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n56\t| 1 | osv | CVE-2025-71176 (PYSEC-2026-1845 / GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g) | Medium (CVSS ~6.8) | no | poetry.lock — pytest 8.3.4 | action-required |\n57\t| 2 | manual-6a | terraform-provider-binaries-not-gitignored | Low | no | .gitignore / infra/.terraform/ | fixed |\n58\t| 3 | manual-6d | tier1-throttle-ip-keying-behind-alb (efficacy, pre-existing, out of diff-scope) | Low | no | src/api/middleware.py:118 | reported-only |\n59\t\n60\t`total_findings: 3`. `osv_findings: 2` in the status JSON is the reconcile convention (unique alias\n61\tid count) for the single logical pytest CVE (row 1).\n62\t\n63\t## Fixes applied\n64\t\n65\t**[fixed] Row 2 — Terraform provider binaries were not gitignored.** `.gitignore` lacked a\n66\t`.terraform/` entry, so `git ls-files --others` pulled ~108 MB of vendored HashiCorp provider\n67\texecutables (`terraform-provider-aws_v5.100.0_x5.exe`, null, random) plus the module cache into the\n68\tdiff-scoped change set — a repo-hygiene / minor supply-chain surface (large signed third-party\n69\tbinaries entering the tree the pipeline hashes and would commit).\n70\t- **Before:** `.gitignore` lines 17–18 = `*.tfstate` / `*.tfvars` only.\n71\t- **After:** added `.terraform/` (line 19). Verified `git check-ignore` now excludes the provider\n72\t  `.exe`s; the change set drops from 8 untracked entries to 2 (test file + `.terraform.lock.hcl`).\n73\t- The provider **lock** `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` is deliberately **not** ignored (pinning provider\n74\t  versions/hashes is good supply-chain practice) — it stays committable.\n75\t\n76\t## Action required (report-only, not auto-fixed)\n77\t\n78\t**Row 1 — pytest 8.3.4 has a vulnerable tmpdir-handling CVE (CVE-2025-71176).**\n79\t- Package: `pytest 8.3.4` (PyPI), a **dev/test-only** dependency (not on the request path, not in the\n80\t  runtime container).\n81\t- CVSS 3.1: `AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:L` ≈ **6.8 (Medium)** — **below** the deploy gate's\n82\t  ≥7.0 High/Critical floor, so it does **not** block. `osv_max_cvss: 6.8`, `osv_waiver: null`.\n83\t- **Safe version: upgrade `pytest` to `>= 9.0.3`.** Per policy, dependency manifests/lockfiles are not\n84\t  modified here; a maintainer bumps `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock`. Not routed to debugging (below the\n85\t  ≥7.0 gate floor); the human decides.\n86\t\n87\t## Could not remediate\n88\t\n89\tNone. No finding required a design decision or escalation.\n90\t\n91\t## Manual security checks (steps 6a–6g)\n92\t\n93\t**6a — Secrets / API-key exposure:** clean. No hardcoded credential literal in any changed file\n94\t(grep + Semgrep p/secrets + Gitleaks all clean on the change set). `.env` is gitignored and untracked;\n95\t`PROJECT.md` diff is only the feature description; no secret in config. The server sets `api_key_id`\n96\tfrom the authenticated principal and never accepts a client-supplied `scope`/`api_key_id`\n97\t(`extra='forbid'` on both request schemas — mass-assignment defense).\n98\t\n99\t**6b — Row-level security:** clean. Every `quotas` query is scoped by `api_key_id` first —\n100\t`list_quotas` (`WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id`), `delete_quota`\n101\t(`WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = … AND metric = …`), `upsert_quota`\n102\t(`ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`). Backstop verified: migration `0003` sets\n103\t`ALTER TABLE quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` + policy `quotas_tenant_isolation`, and\n104\t`scoped_transaction` sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL set_config(...)`\n105\t(`src/db/session.py:58-85`). Efficacy-correct (U-02): the app role owns the table, so FORCE is\n106\trequired and present — a non-FORCE policy would be inert.\n107\t\n108\t**6c — Input / output sanitization:** clean.\n109\t- DELETE query params validated by `QuotaDeleteParams` (anchored `constr` allowlists\n110\t  `^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128/64}$`, ReDoS-safe, `extra='forbid'`) before the handler — an injection\n111\t  payload (`' OR 1=1--`) is rejected at the boundary (422), never reaching the sink (AC9).\n112\t- GET accepts no body/query/path parameter — no injectable input.\n113\t- All new SQL uses SQLAlchemy `text()` with bound parameters only — no string interpolation. ast-grep\n114\t  structural check for `session.execute(text(f\"…\"))` in the repo: **0 hits** (confirms AC15).\n115\t- Output: `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` projects only `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}`\n116\t  (no `api_key_id`/timestamps). JSON API, no HTML/JS/URL sink — no output-encoding exposure.\n117\t\n118\t**6d — STRIDE mechanism verification (10/10 present + efficacy-correct, 0 missing):**\n119\t1. Spoofing → `_require_admin_and_throttled` = `require_api_key` (Argon2id) + `scope=='admin'`→403 — `routes/quotas.py:35-52`. ✓\n120\t2. Tampering/SQLi → anchored `constr` + parameterized `text()` — `schemas/quotas.py:15-16`, `quotas_repo.py:205-214`. ✓\n121\t3. Tampering/mass-assignment → `ConfigDict(extra='forbid')`, server-set `api_key_id` — `schemas/quotas.py:60`. ✓\n122\t4. Repudiation → `quota.delete` INFO (userId, action, customer_id[redacted], metric, requestId) — `quota_service.py:116-122`. ✓\n123\t5. Info-disclosure (GET) → minimal `response_model` + `api_key_id`-scoped SELECT + FORCE RLS — `routes/quotas.py:68`, `quotas_repo.py:161-187`. ✓\n124\t6. Info-disclosure (safe-error) → `handle_unexpected_error` returns generic `{code:internal}` 500, detail logged server-side only; `scoped_transaction` rolls back (fail-closed, no partial DELETE) — `errors.py:97-118`, `db/session.py:65`. ✓ (AC19)\n125\t7. DoS (flood) → Tier-1 IP throttle + Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` bucket — `middleware.py`, `rate_limit.py:136-154`. ✓ (efficacy: see below)\n126\t8. EoP (function-level) → `scope=='admin'`→403, `quota.forbidden` logged — `routes/quotas.py:44-51`. ✓\n127\t9. EoP (IDOR/BOLA) → `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS → cross-tenant DELETE matches 0 rows → 404 — `quotas_repo.py`, `db/session.py`, `0003`. ✓\n128\t10. Tampering (`usage_rollup` integrity) → `delete_quota` issues **only** a DELETE on `quotas`, never touches `usage_rollup` — `quotas_repo.py:205-214`. ✓\n129\t\n130\tEfficacy questions (U-02) answered:\n131\t- **Async runtime:** no CPU-hard KDF or blocking sync SDK call on the event loop in the changed handlers.\n132\t  ast-grep for `argon2.*`/`bcrypt.*` in the changed src: **0 hits**; the one `boto3.client` in the tree\n133\t  is `src/config/secrets.py` (pre-existing, startup-time, not in this change set). All handler DB I/O\n134\t  goes through the async session. ✓\n135\t- **DB privilege:** FORCE RLS present + app-role owns the table (verified above). ✓\n136\t- **Contract drift:** the safe-error scrubber (`handle_unexpected_error`) is a global catch-all that\n137\t  covers the two new DB-I/O paths (AC19); response body carries no stack/SQL/type/path. ✓\n138\t- **Topology (the one efficacy warning, row 3):** the Tier-1 pre-auth throttle keys its bucket on\n139\t  `request.client.host` (`middleware.py:118`) and no `--proxy-headers`/`forwarded-allow-ips` trust is\n140\t  configured, so **behind the ALB** Tier-1 would bucket per-ALB-node rather than per-real-client. This\n141\t  is **pre-existing** middleware **not introduced by this diff** (the only middleware change here is\n142\t  adding `\"DELETE\"` to CORS `allow_methods`), and for these admin routes the **effective** anti-abuse\n143\t  control is **Tier-2**, which keys on `str(principal.api_key_id)` (`rate_limit.py:153`) — topology-\n144\t  independent and proven per-principal by AC12. The LB readiness path `/health` is correctly exempt\n145\t  from Tier-1 (`_TIER1_EXEMPT_PATHS`). Recorded as a Low warning for the pre-existing Tier-1 IP-keying;\n146\t  not a blocker for this feature.\n147\t\n148\t**6e — Log-sink safety:** clean. `quota.delete` / `quota.forbidden` use the structlog facade with\n149\tdiscrete fields; `customer_id` is facade-redacted (AC16) and the allowlist pattern precludes\n150\tnewline/CR injection into log lines. No request body, password, token, or unredacted PII logged. The\n151\terror handler logs `error.message`/`error.type` **server-side only** (never in the response) — acceptable.\n152\t\n153\t**6f — STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation:** `stride_new_threats: 0`. The surface-delta hint\n154\tmatches the diff exactly. New surfaces (GET /v1/quotas, DELETE /v1/quotas, the CORS `DELETE` method\n155\taddition) are each already covered by the plan's threat model — the plan was authored for this feature.\n156\tThe CORS `DELETE` addition has no live effect (empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API). No new\n157\toutbound call, subprocess, deserialization, table, or un-modeled entry point. Addendum below is empty.\n158\t\n159\t**6g — ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation (AC18, delegated to security):** `reconciled: true`.\n160\t- **Triggered chapters** (from plan `## ASVS Compliance` + diff): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V12, V13, V14, V16.\n161\t- **L1 + L2 (universal)** verified on every triggered chapter; **in-scope L3** = V8.2.x object-level\n162\t  authorization (IDOR/BOLA), verified via the `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS + the cross-tenant-\n163\t  DELETE→404 test (AC8). Key requirement evidence: 1.2.4 (parameterized DELETE SQL), 2.2.1/2.4.1\n164\t  (validation + anti-automation Tier-2), 6.2.x (Argon2id API-key auth, reused), 8.2.1/8.2.2/8.2.3/8.4.1\n165\t  (admin gate + tenant isolation on read/delete), 14.3.x (minimal GET response, no sensitive store),\n166\t  15.3.1/15.3.3 (minimal field set + mass-assignment `extra='forbid'`), 16.2.1/16.5.1/16.5.3\n167\t  (`quota.delete` audit + generic 404/500 fail-closed envelope). `reqs_verified: 14`.\n168\t- **`n/a`** (correctly, per plan): V3, V5, V7, V9, V10, V11, V15, V17 — server-to-server API, no\n169\t  browser/cookies, no files, no sessions/JWT/OAuth, no new crypto, no new concurrency-integrity\n170\t  guarantee, no WebRTC.\n171\t- **No unwaived L1/L2/in-scope-L3 code/config item is unmet.** No `doc_advisory` items surfaced. No\n172\t  human waiver in `.pipeline/waivers.json` (file absent) — none needed. `l1_l2_missing: []`,\n173\t  `l3_in_scope_missing: []`.\n174\t\n175\t## Input-surface reconciliation\n176\t\n177\t`reconciled: true`. Two implemented input sources, both controlled: `DELETE /v1/quotas` has a\n178\tvalidation contract (`QuotaDeleteParams`) **and** a Tier-2 rate-limit (AC12); `GET /v1/quotas` accepts\n179\tno input parameter and has the Tier-2 rate-limit. `declared: 2`, `implemented: 2`, `uncontrolled: []`.\n180\t\n181\t## Data-surface reconciliation\n182\t\n183\t`reconciled: true`. The feature stores **no new field** — GET reads, DELETE removes existing rows. The\n184\tlisted/deleted columns (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`) are pre-classified non-sensitive\n185\toperational config already at rest under RDS SSE (documented `data_protection_waiver` in\n186\t`acceptance.md`). `classified: 0`, `sensitive: 0`, `unprotected: []`.\n187\t\n188\t## STRIDE delta addendum\n189\t\n190\t_Empty — the diff introduces no attack surface the plan's threat model did not already cover._\n191\t\n192\t## Out-of-scope / informational\n193\t\n194\t- **Gitleaks 128 hits — all outside the change set.** 124 in gitignored `.venv/` (botocore example\n195\t  fixtures, vendored libs), 2 in `.pipeline/archive/` + prior-feature `docs/`, and 2 in **prior-feature**\n196\t  test fixtures (`tests/test_schemas_events.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` —\n197\t  merged in features 1/3, not in this diff). Zero hits in any quota change-set file. Not this feature's\n198\t  responsibility; noted for the record.\n199\t"}]},"uuid":"de4709f3-08a0-4fed-ac98-3b5d7f746276","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:51:43.387Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"106023b4-bc61-41fc-86f6-c1c245e85fa6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
