{"parentUuid":"55890b2e-5c58-43d8-82b9-1a3b6b487610","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019ccdbn3oCdDp5Zt6tVCNoD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t{\n2\t  \"quality_ok\": false,\n3\t  \"quality_waiver\": null,\n4\t  \"ran_at\": \"2026-07-10T03:45:42Z\",\n5\t  \"mutation\": {\n6\t    \"tool\": \"mutmut\",\n7\t    \"configured_scope\": [\"src/repositories/quotas_repo.py\", \"src/services/quota_service.py\", \"src/api/routes/quotas.py\", \"src/api/schemas/quotas.py\"],\n8\t    \"scope\": [],\n9\t    \"score\": null,\n10\t    \"killed\": 0,\n11\t    \"survived\": 0,\n12\t    \"threshold\": null,\n13\t    \"note\": \"mutmut 3.6.0 is installed but refuses to run natively on Windows: `python -m mutmut run --paths-to-mutate src/services/quota_service.py --max-children 1` this session printed 'To run mutmut on Windows, please use the WSL. Native windows support is tracked in issue https://github.com/boxed/mutmut/issues/397' and exited without mutating anything (verified this session, actual_scope=[] -- the run never started, not a silently-shrunk scope). This is the same pre-documented win32 gap noted in pipeline-ci.yml's mutation job comment ('the local pipeline honestly skips it ... the measurement just never happened on win32, two M3-series runs in a row'). The CI mutation job exists in .github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml but is gated `if: false` pending <MUTATION_CMD>/<MUTATION_SCOPE> being filled -- mutation coverage for this feature has genuinely never run anywhere yet. quality_ok is honestly false rather than claiming a scope that was never mutated (WS3-1: scope=[] cannot cover configured_scope, so quality_ok:true would be dishonest here).\"\n14\t  },\n15\t  \"adversarial_review\": {\n16\t    \"gaps\": [\n17\t      {\n18\t        \"area\": \"AC12 / rate limiting\",\n19\t        \"gap\": \"test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal proves the per-principal-not-per-IP dimension well (the discriminating shape), but only exercises GET's throttle exhaustion directly (principal A's second GET 429s); DELETE is only proven to NOT be throttled for principal B (which still has capacity), never driven to its own 429. A route-specific throttle-key bug on DELETE alone (e.g. a copy-paste that hard-codes a different bucket name) would not be caught.\",\n20\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n21\t      },\n22\t      {\n23\t        \"area\": \"AC9 / DELETE validation - query-param type coercion\",\n24\t        \"gap\": \"The 422 tests cover missing field, invalid customer_id shape, injection payload, and an unknown extra param, but never a wrong-TYPE value for a query param that pydantic could silently coerce (e.g. metric as a list via repeated ?metric=a&metric=b, or a customer_id supplied as an array-like bracket syntax). FastAPI's Query() binding for a str field on repeated params is worth a boundary test given DELETE takes only query params (no body) and typed coercion mistakes are exactly the class of bug allowlist-based schemas are meant to catch.\",\n25\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n26\t      },\n27\t      {\n28\t        \"area\": \"quotas_repo.list_quotas / delete_quota - ordering under NULL or duplicate collisions\",\n29\t        \"gap\": \"AC1's ordering test seeds three distinct (customer_id, metric) pairs; it never seeds two rows differing only by metric under case-insensitive-adjacent values (e.g. 'API' vs 'api') to prove the RDS default collation genuinely produces a stable order across runs (plan's own open question 2 flags this as an accepted risk, not resolved) -- current tests can't distinguish 'stable because ORDER BY is present' from 'stable because the specific seeded values happen to sort unambiguously under any collation'.\",\n30\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n31\t      },\n32\t      {\n33\t        \"area\": \"AC19 / GET safe-error path\",\n34\t        \"gap\": \"The GET forced-error test monkeypatches quota_service.list_quotas at the service layer, which is one level above the actual DB I/O (quotas_repo.list_quotas). It proves the route -> error-handler wiring, but doesn't force a failure inside the repository's own text()-execute call (e.g. a real asyncpg DBAPIError) to prove the repository layer itself doesn't leak a raw SQLSTATE/DSN fragment before the service-level catch. The DELETE variant has the same shape but is partially compensated by its own fail-closed row-survival assertion, which does exercise real DB state.\",\n35\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n36\t      },\n37\t      {\n38\t        \"area\": \"Mutation coverage\",\n39\t        \"gap\": \"No mutation run has ever executed against quotas_repo.py/quota_service.py/routes/quotas.py/schemas/quotas.py (see mutation.note) -- so 100%-branch-covered lines in these modules are unverified against e.g. an off-by-one in the ORDER BY clause, a flipped 404-vs-204 boundary condition, or a swapped AND/OR in delete_quota's WHERE clause. Line/branch coverage alone cannot catch a mutant that changes behavior without changing which lines execute (e.g. AND -> OR in the WHERE clause would still hit the same lines).\",\n40\t        \"severity\": \"medium\"\n41\t      }\n42\t    ]\n43\t  }\n44\t}\n45\t"}]},"uuid":"18d76600-19a4-4c4f-ada9-ec63c60752b5","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:06.574Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"55890b2e-5c58-43d8-82b9-1a3b6b487610","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
