{"parentUuid":"406553ab-ff62-43d6-bb7a-9596cdefcec4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshYBwz7KVSVqcaRMygv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XNshP4ev3dq5CXc3nArGBW","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":876,"cache_read_input_tokens":61250,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":876,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcshYB4Qa9yy8qAzt5YJr","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5ce38c4f-7b1d-4bf4-8630-b447a8bef00e","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:24.166Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"5ce38c4f-7b1d-4bf4-8630-b447a8bef00e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XNshP4ev3dq5CXc3nArGBW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tUnit and fast component tests (no live Postgres/Redis) for the `src/` package,\n6\tplus the `tests/integration/` suite (real Postgres/Redis via testcontainers,\n7\tand real HTTP/k6 load). Mirrors `src/`'s layering: schema/crypto/time-window\n8\tunit tests here, endpoint/migration/concurrency/perf tests under `integration/`.\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures for the non-integration suite. |\n15\t| `test_app_smoke.py` | App-construction-level tests needing no DB/Redis: liveness, OpenAPI exposure, unauthenticated-denial/error-envelope shape. |\n16\t| `test_auth_api_key.py` | Split-token parsing and the in-process verification cache (Argon2id-vs-p95 cache mechanism). |\n17\t| `test_crypto.py` | `src/crypto` facade: Argon2id hash/verify, constant-time compare. |\n18\t| `test_csv_export.py` | `src/api/csv_export.py` unit tests: `escape_csv_text_cell` (formula-trigger prefixing incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, control-char stripping), RFC 4180 quoting via `csv.writer`, `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatting (no scientific notation, UTC ISO-8601). |\n19\t| `test_dast_context_documented.py` | Asserts the DAST scanner auth context (header + token shape) is documented somewhere a DAST job's config can read it. |\n20\t| `test_db_session_isolation.py` | Regression guard for the `READ COMMITTED` isolation pin in `src/db/session.py` — the dependency the quota lock-then-read atomicity in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::read_tenant_quota_state_locked` relies on. |\n21\t| `test_dependency_pins.py` | Security-regression guard against a starlette CVE-carrying downgrade (pinned version stays at the patched release). |\n22\t| `test_logging_redaction.py` | A raw `customer_id` (or other sensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line regardless of call site. |\n23\t| `test_rate_limit_fail_open.py` | Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade in `src/auth/rate_limit.py`. |\n24\t| `test_schemas_events.py` | Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest`. |\n25\t| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection). |\n26\t| `test_schemas_usage.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams`. |\n27\t| `test_schemas_usage_export.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageExportQueryParams`: all-filters-optional, the `from`/`from_` alias binding, naive-datetime rejection, `from<=to` and `[now-90d, now+1h]` bound enforcement, `extra=\"forbid\"` rejecting unknown/injected fields. |\n28\t| `test_slo_alarms_defined.py` | Static assertion that the declared SLO burn-rate + canary CloudWatch alarms exist in the Terraform source with the exact names `deploy.yml` expects. |\n29\t| `test_time_windows.py` | Tests for the UTC hour-flooring helper (`floor_to_hour_utc`) shared by `events_service` and `usage_service`. |\n30\t| `test_usage_export_service.py` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` unit tests: `prepare_export` cap-boundary (exactly-at-cap passes, cap+1 → 422) and fail-closed non-cap-error propagation (AC22); `stream_export_csv` header-first-on-empty-result, audit-log fields (no raw `customer_id`), `completed=False` on a mid-stream failure, and the chunk-batching regression guard (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK`). |\n31\t| `integration/` | Tests requiring a real Postgres/Redis (testcontainers) or a live HTTP process — see `tests/integration/README.md`. |\n32\t\n33\t## Relationships\n34\t\n35\t- Unit tests here import directly from `src.*` modules (schemas, crypto, auth, time\n36\t  windows) with no network/DB dependency — fast, run on every commit.\n37\t- `integration/` depends on Docker (testcontainers for Postgres/Redis, and for\n38\t  `test_perf_k6_load.py`, the `grafana/k6` image) and is slower; both suites are\n39\t  collected together by `pytest --cov=src --cov-branch` (per `CLAUDE.md`).\n40\t- Test IDs referenced in docstrings (`AC1`, `AC-PERF`, etc.) trace to\n41\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`'s acceptance criteria for the feature that introduced them.\n42\t"}]},"uuid":"798a62c0-3b80-4365-a0ca-3cf6158b0fc4","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:24.205Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5ce38c4f-7b1d-4bf4-8630-b447a8bef00e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"406553ab-ff62-43d6-bb7a-9596cdefcec4","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CGNfty1Ukm27sqTKK1gEjL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/services/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tBusiness logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity), usage aggregation, and time-window calculations. Orchestrates repositories and enforces domain invariants.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_service.py` | `create_event(principal, payload)` — inserts an event, checks the caller's quota (if any) on the winning-insert branch, and increments the hourly counter, all in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Raises `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`) when `R + Q > L`, which rolls back the event insert. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n12\t| `usage_service.py` | `get_usage(principal, query)` — reads the aggregated counter for the `(customer_id, metric, window)` bucket in `query` (a `UsageQueryParams`); returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n13\t| `usage_export_service.py` | `prepare_export(principal, params)` — the pre-flight row-cap check: a `COUNT(*)` in its own transaction, raising a plain 422 `HTTPException` over `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS` (100,000) *before* any response byte; any other (non-cap) error propagates uncaught to the error-envelope boundary (fail-closed 500, no stream ever started). `stream_export_csv(principal, params)` — the `StreamingResponse` body generator: opens its own tenant-scoped transaction (Starlette pulls it only after the route returns), yields the header row first always (so an empty result is a 200 header-only CSV, never 404), then one CSV-encoded row per streamed rollup at constant memory (a reused `io.StringIO`, drained and reset per row), and logs one `usage.export` audit event in a `finally` block (fires even on a client disconnect or a mid-stream error). |\n14\t| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n15\t| `time_windows.py` | `floor_to_hour_utc(timestamp: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by `events_service` and `usage_service`. |\n16\t\n17\t## Relationships\n18\t\n19\t**Public surface:**\n20\t- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, usage_export, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n21\t\n22\t**Dependencies:**\n23\t- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n24\t- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n25\t- `usage_export_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` (`count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`) and `src/api/csv_export.py` (the column contract + formula-escape facade) — it owns the `csv.writer`/`io.StringIO` streaming mechanics, `csv_export.py` owns only the encoding/escaping contract.\n26\t- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n27\t- All services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs (the export has no scope gate — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data).\n28\t- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n29\t\n30\t**Transaction boundary:**\n31\t- `create_event` wraps the event insert, the quota check, and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n32\t- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`) and the quota check passes, the counter increments exactly once.\n33\t- If the insert loses (duplicate key), the quota is never consulted and neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n34\t- If the quota check rejects (`R + Q > L`), raising `QuotaExceededError` propagates out of the transaction context and rolls it back — the event insert is undone and the counter is never touched (no partial write).\n35\t- `upsert_tenant_quota` wraps the quota upsert in its own transaction; a single `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0)` reports create-vs-replace with no second round-trip.\n36\t\n37\t## Notes\n38\t\n39\t**Idempotency guarantee:**\n40\t- The unique constraint `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` on the `events` table is the source of truth.\n41\t- Exactly one of N concurrent identical requests will succeed; the rest get a duplicate-key constraint violation (caught, no exception raised to handler) and fall through to a replay branch.\n42\t- The replay branch reads the original event from the table and returns it, so the caller sees a consistent result across retries.\n43\t- Recorded in the plan as the **AC-CONCURRENCY** mechanism: 50 concurrent same-key POSTs produce exactly one row and 49 get the replay response (200 vs. 201).\n44\t\n45\t**Counter atomicity:**\n46\t- The event insert and the rollup upsert are in one transaction, so both commit or both roll back.\n47\t- This means a counter never gets incremented without the event being persisted (no partial writes).\n48\t- Also means a duplicate event never increments the counter (no double-counting).\n49\t- The counter uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` with `total_quantity + EXCLUDED.total_quantity` to handle the increment (PostgreSQL's row-level conflict resolution, atomic at the SQL level).\n50\t\n51\t**Time-window semantics:**\n52\t- A timestamp is floored to its hour (UTC) to get the `window_start`. E.g., `2026-07-06T14:35:42Z` → `2026-07-06T14:00:00Z`.\n53\t- The floor is done explicitly in Python (`ts.replace(minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)`) rather than in the database, because PostgreSQL's `date_trunc('hour', ts)` is STABLE (depends on session timezone), not IMMUTABLE, so it cannot be used in a stored generated column.\n54\t- All windows are in UTC; clients must provide timezone-aware ISO-8601 timestamps on GET.\n55\t\n56\t**Scoping by api_key_id:**\n57\t- Both services receive the authenticated `api_key_id` from the route guard (set in `request.state`).\n58\t- Both services pass it to the repository layer, which includes it in the WHERE clause (e.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id`).\n59\t- This is the primary RLS mechanism; the PostgreSQL RLS policy is the backstop.\n60\t"}]},"uuid":"1b082b6b-c51e-4eef-8550-2d030398ac91","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:24.208Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"406553ab-ff62-43d6-bb7a-9596cdefcec4","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"1b082b6b-c51e-4eef-8550-2d030398ac91","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshYBwz7KVSVqcaRMygv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CNzdJsrn5d5jPvEToJo42j","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":876,"cache_read_input_tokens":61250,"output_tokens":501,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":876},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":501,"cache_read_input_tokens":61250,"cache_creation_input_tokens":876,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":876,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcshYB4Qa9yy8qAzt5YJr","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"abd4f483-63bb-49cc-b831-6807cf4ca57a","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:24.374Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"abd4f483-63bb-49cc-b831-6807cf4ca57a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CNzdJsrn5d5jPvEToJo42j","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/integration/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tIntegration tests that exercise the app against real dependencies: Postgres and\n6\tRedis via testcontainers, a live out-of-process uvicorn for perf/load tests, and\n7\tAlembic migrations run against a scratch database. Complements the fast unit\n8\tsuite in `tests/` (no live DB/Redis there).\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures: testcontainer Postgres/Redis setup, the FastAPI test client, seeded `api_keys` rows. |\n15\t| `test_concurrency.py` | 50 concurrent same-`idempotency_key` POSTs create exactly one `events` row (idempotency under concurrency). |\n16\t| `test_data_protection.py` | `api_keys.secret_hash` is persisted as an Argon2id hash, never plaintext; the normal auth path still verifies end to end. |\n17\t| `test_events_endpoint.py` | `POST /v1/events` integration tests (create, replay, validation, auth). |\n18\t| `test_events_quota_enforcement.py` | `POST /v1/events` quota-check integration tests: unlimited-without-a-quota, under/at/over-limit, replay-bypasses-quota, mid-window quota change, throttle-vs-quota distinct error codes. |\n19\t| `test_health_readiness.py` | `/health/ready` against a live, migrated Postgres. |\n20\t| `test_migrations.py` | Migration round-trip (`0001`/`0002`) on a prod-shaped seeded dataset, own scratch testcontainer. |\n21\t| `test_perf_k6_load.py` | Sustained k6 load (via Docker) against a real out-of-process uvicorn; drives both the no-quota baseline and the quota-active scenario at equal worker budget for the AC20 relative p95 comparison. |\n22\t| `test_perf_smoke.py` | Smoke-sized perf check (no k6/Locust dependency) against a live uvicorn process. |\n23\t| `test_quota_concurrency.py` | N concurrent distinct-`idempotency_key` posts against a quota cap `L` never drive the rollup total above `L` (`FOR UPDATE` row-lock serialization proof). |\n24\t| `test_quota_migration.py` | Migration `0003` (`quotas` table + `api_keys.scope`) round-trip and constraint re-enforcement. |\n25\t| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n26\t| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. |\n27\t| `test_rate_limit.py` | Tier-2 (`api_key_id`-keyed) rate limiting: two principals on one IP get independent buckets; one principal across two IPs shares one bucket. |\n28\t| `test_seed_api_key_script.py` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` provisions a key against a real database, including the `--admin` flag setting `scope='admin'` (default `scope='ingest'`). |\n29\t| `test_usage_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage` integration tests (aggregation, tenant isolation). |\n30\t| `test_usage_export_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` integration tests: header-only-CSV on an empty result, per-filter narrowing, deterministic ordering, two-tenant isolation, row-cap 422 with no partial body, formula-injection escape end-to-end, response headers (content-type/filename/nosniff/no-store), streaming-not-buffered (multi-chunk) sanity, OpenAPI-schema exposure (AC19), the seeded DAST key calling the export via `test_export_seeded_dast_key_can_call_the_export` (AC20), and the fail-closed pre-flight 500 on a forced `COUNT` error (AC22). |\n31\t| `test_usage_export_perf.py` | Real-Postgres-testcontainer p95 timing sanity check for the export at the 100,000-row cap (AC16) — a 10-sample stable measurement asserting the human-confirmed `p95 <= 3,000ms` bound (not a k6 load test). |\n32\t| `k6/` | k6 load-test scripts driven by `test_perf_k6_load.py` — see `k6/README.md`. |\n33\t\n34\t## Relationships\n35\t\n36\t- All DB-backed tests share the Postgres/Redis testcontainer fixtures from `conftest.py`,\n37\t  except `test_migrations.py` and `test_quota_migration.py`, which own a scratch\n38\t  testcontainer independently (they drive the migration lifecycle itself: down to a\n39\t  prior revision and back up, which the shared fixture's already-migrated database\n40\t  can't support).\n41\t- `test_perf_k6_load.py` and `k6/load_events_quota.js` work as a pair: the Python test\n42\t  starts uvicorn, seeds fixture data (including quota rows for the quota-active run),\n43\t  invokes the k6 script via Docker, and asserts against the JSON summary it produces.\n44\t- Docstring AC references (`AC7`, `AC13`, `AC16`, `AC20`, etc.) trace to\n45\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`.\n46\t"}]},"uuid":"acbe0b11-c9c7-4d75-b9db-1c7351a20b4a","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:24.407Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"abd4f483-63bb-49cc-b831-6807cf4ca57a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
