{"parentUuid":"0f4779ae-7c21-404d-8850-ebbad2550f16","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018WuxsMGKp2Gwuf6AezHe4D","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly\n2\t\n3\tUsage-metering ingestion API. See `PROJECT.md` for the product spec and\n4\t`docs/system_architecture.md` for the implementation overview.\n5\t\n6\t## Quickstart\n7\t\n8\t```bash\n9\tpoetry install\n10\tpoetry run alembic upgrade head\n11\tpoetry run uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000\n12\t```\n13\t\n14\t`GET /health` returns 200 with no dependencies (liveness). `GET /health/ready`\n15\tchecks the database connection and migration head (readiness).\n16\t"}]},"uuid":"38ef55e4-7600-4b7a-8d28-48bcdd2ca350","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:53:41.946Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0f4779ae-7c21-404d-8850-ebbad2550f16","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
