{"parentUuid":"bc3655ff-a551-441c-ad66-875a08c21165","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WnZFM5iS8D1RPHS3mAiERk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tfeature: quota administration — list + delete (GET /v1/quotas, DELETE /v1/quotas)\n3\tcriteria_total: 19\n4\tdelegated_criteria: [AC18]\n5\tderived_from: .pipeline/requirements.md (Resolved; zero Open) + PROJECT.md + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness + ASVS-DET T2-2 (safe-error handling)\n6\tnotes: >\n7\t  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a test\n8\t  (criteria_covered). The deploy gate requires criteria_covered.total == criteria_total and that\n9\t  every delegated id appears in delegated_criteria (only `security` is a valid delegate). AC18 is\n10\t  delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation is its deliverable, not a test assertion), so\n11\t  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\".\n12\t  AC19 (safe-error handling, ASVS-DET T2-2) was added in the plan-audit revision pass: both GET and\n13\t  DELETE do live DB I/O that can raise, and the project has an exact precedent test shape\n14\t  (tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed,\n15\t  feature 1's AC19). It is a real test-backed criterion, NOT delegated.\n16\t  No data_protection criterion: this feature stores NO new field (GET reads, DELETE removes rows);\n17\t  the rows it lists/deletes are pre-classified non-sensitive operational config already at rest under\n18\t  RDS SSE — data_protection_waiver: this feature stores no new stored field; customer_id / metric /\n19\t  limit_per_window are pre-classified non-sensitive operational config covered by RDS SSE\n20\t  (storage-level), no field-level KDF/KMS applies.\n21\t  No migration-reversibility criterion: no schema change, no new alembic/versions/ file (asserted\n22\t  negatively by AC14).\n23\t  No performance / k6 criterion: the brief pins \"no new perf budget beyond existing p95 targets\";\n24\t  both routes are admin-only, low-traffic (one indexed SELECT / one indexed DELETE). The binding perf\n25\t  constraint is the negative one (AC14 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched).\n26\t  GET /v1/quotas has NO request body/query/path parameter, so it carries no validation AC (nothing to\n27\t  validate); its rate-limit control is AC12 and its authz/auth are AC4/AC5. DELETE's input surface\n28\t  carries both a validation (AC9, non-waivable) and a rate-limit (AC12) criterion.\n29\t---\n30\t\n31\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n32\t|---|---|---|---|\n33\t| AC1 | `GET /v1/quotas` (admin key) → **200** with the full unpaginated list of the caller's tenant quotas, each row **exactly** `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` (no `api_key_id`/timestamps), deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)` ascending | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` (`QuotaResponse`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields` (seeds a multi-row set, asserts order + exact keys) |\n34\t| AC2 | GET tenant isolation: tenant A's list contains **only** tenant A's rows and never tenant B's (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; FORCE RLS is the backstop) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_is_tenant_isolated` (two-tenant seed; A's list excludes B) |\n35\t| AC3 | GET with an empty quota set → **200** with an empty JSON array `[]` (never 404) | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list` |\n36\t| AC4 | GET with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403**, envelope `code: forbidden` (admin scope required; no ingest read path) | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (`_require_admin_and_throttled`), `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n37\t| AC5 | GET with missing/malformed/revoked auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_requires_auth` |\n38\t| AC6 | `DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y` (admin key, existing quota) → **204 No Content**, empty body; the `(customer_id, metric)` row under the caller's tenant is removed (subsequent GET no longer lists it; row count for that key decreases by one) | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row` |\n39\t| AC7 | DELETE for a `(customer_id, metric)` with **no** quota in the caller's tenant → **404** with the standard error envelope `code: not_found` (explicit, not silently idempotent) | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py` (`_STATUS_TO_CODE[404]`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope` |\n40\t| AC8 | DELETE cross-tenant isolation (IDOR/BOLA): tenant A deleting a `(customer_id, metric)` that exists only under tenant B → **404** (invisible), and tenant B's row is **still present** afterward | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` (FORCE RLS) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant` (two-tenant; A→404, B's row intact) |\n41\t| AC9 | DELETE validation (**non-waivable**): `customer_id`/`metric` outside the anchored allowlist, missing, wrong type, or an unknown extra query param → **422** `validation_failed`; an injection payload (e.g. `' OR 1=1--`) in `customer_id`/`metric` is rejected at the schema boundary and never reaches the `DELETE` SQL sink | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` (`QuotaDeleteParams`, reused `CustomerId`/`Metric`, `extra='forbid'`) | `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py` (unit: allowlist/injection/oversized/extra-field) + `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_validation_rejections` |\n42\t| AC10 | DELETE with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403** `forbidden` | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (`_require_admin_and_throttled`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n43\t| AC11 | DELETE with missing/malformed auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_requires_auth` |\n44\t| AC12 | Rate limit: **both** GET and DELETE `/v1/quotas` are throttled by the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token bucket (principal-keyed, post-auth); two admin principals sharing one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal` (two-principals-one-IP shape on GET and DELETE) |\n45\t| AC13 | No usage-data side effects on delete + no `POST /v1/events` behavior change: deleting a quota removes **only** the cap — `usage_rollup` for that `(customer, metric)` is **unchanged**; a subsequent `POST /v1/events` for the now-uncapped `(customer, metric)` is accepted **201 unlimited** (same as never-capped) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`delete_quota` touches only `quotas`), `src/services/events_service.py` (unchanged) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped` |\n46\t| AC14 | No schema change / no new migration: GET+DELETE operate on the existing `quotas` table; **no** file added under `alembic/versions/`; `PUT /v1/quotas`, `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, and their existing tests are unchanged | repo-wide (negative) | Existing suites pass unchanged; assert no new `alembic/versions/*.py` beyond `0001–0003` |\n47\t| AC15 | All new quota SQL (list `SELECT`, `DELETE`) uses parameterized `text()` bind params only and filters `api_key_id = :principal.api_key_id`; the `DELETE` is confined to the caller's tenant by the explicit filter + `quotas_tenant_isolation` **FORCE** RLS backstop | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant` (RLS/filter) + security 6c (Semgrep: no string-built SQL) |\n48\t| AC16 | Audit logging: a successful DELETE emits exactly one `quota.delete` **INFO** (`userId`, `action=\"delete\"`, `customer_id` [facade-redacted to `***redacted***`], `metric`, `requestId`) via the structlog facade; a scope-denied GET or DELETE emits the existing `quota.forbidden` **WARNING** | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/logging` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged` (capsys: `quota.delete` present + `customer_id` redacted; `quota.forbidden` on ingest-key call) |\n49\t| AC17 (DAST-readiness) | The served `/openapi.json` includes **both** `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` matching the implemented routes/schemas; the DAST auth context documents the **admin**-scoped seeded key (`seed_api_key.py --admin`) with the `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` scheme | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `.pipeline/plan.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas` + `tests/test_dast_context_documented.py` |\n50\t| AC18 | ASVS 5.0.0 L1/L2 (+ in-scope L3: V8.2.x object-level authorization / BOLA) reconciliation across the change set — triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/V14/V16 met or waived | security stage (`asvs` reconciliation block) | delegated: `security` (covered:false at the testing stage) |\n51\t| AC19 (safe-error, ASVS-DET T2-2) | Safe-error / fail-closed on live DB I/O: a **forced internal error** during the GET list read **and** during the DELETE path returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (`code: internal`, `requestId` present, **no** stack trace / SQL fragment / exception type / internal path leaked). The DELETE additionally **fails closed** — the transaction rolls back, so the targeted quota row is **not** actually/partially deleted. Mirrors feature 1's `POST /v1/events` precedent | `src/api/errors.py` (`handle_unexpected_error` catch-all), `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/db/session.py` (`scoped_transaction` rollback) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope` + `::test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed` (monkeypatch the repo fn to raise, `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)`, assert `500`/`code:internal`/no-leak; DELETE asserts the pre-seeded row survives) — same shape as `tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed` |\n52\t"}]},"uuid":"45816c76-d0a0-4aad-9ef3-b386653e0860","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:54:06.700Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bc3655ff-a551-441c-ad66-875a08c21165","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
