{"parentUuid":"08621024-36cc-45f8-93e9-21c04c9b0e54","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccshg9JDDgev7rgDHzCnH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QeN3LyG8wmbgX9yYxB9RM5","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md","offset":44,"limit":15},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1660,"cache_read_input_tokens":99996,"output_tokens":246,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1660},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":246,"cache_read_input_tokens":99996,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1660,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1660,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccshg6xaM9mvBX5xvefdL","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"c3ec448f-25ef-41ab-9742-13fde3be3ab5","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:55:12.848Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"c3ec448f-25ef-41ab-9742-13fde3be3ab5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QeN3LyG8wmbgX9yYxB9RM5","type":"tool_result","content":"44\t\n45\t## Notes\n46\t\n47\t**ON CONFLICT pattern:**\n48\t- The idempotency mechanism uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING RETURNING id, ...`.\n49\t- If the unique constraint is violated, the INSERT returns no rows.\n50\t- The service layer checks `if result` — if a row was returned, this request won the insert; if not, a duplicate is detected.\n51\t\n52\t**RLS context setup:**\n53\t- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n54\t- This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n55\t- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\n56\t\n57\t**Quota lock-then-read pattern (why it's two statements, not one):**\n58\t- `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` deliberately issues the `FOR UPDATE` lock on `quotas` and the `usage_rollup` read as two separate statements, not a single `LEFT JOIN ... FOR UPDATE OF q` query."}]},"uuid":"a660f619-c0c7-4eb6-b0ca-f42dca76bab0","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:55:12.866Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c3ec448f-25ef-41ab-9742-13fde3be3ab5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"a660f619-c0c7-4eb6-b0ca-f42dca76bab0","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshgVCHoaohWNAYzymku","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016Ky3trJqheY4GhAbZTiR5b","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md","old_string":"**RLS context setup:**","new_string":"**DELETE ... RETURNING pattern:**\n- `delete_quota` issues a single parameterized `DELETE ... WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric RETURNING customer_id`.\n- Whether a row was returned (not a row-count check) is what the service uses to distinguish \"removed\" from \"nothing there to remove\" — avoids a separate existence check and the TOCTOU gap that would introduce between check and delete.\n- A cross-tenant call matches zero rows here (the `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS backstop), which the service maps to the same 404 as a truly-absent quota — the BOLA-safe behavior.\n\n**RLS context setup:**"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":662,"cache_read_input_tokens":101656,"output_tokens":390,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":662},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":390,"cache_read_input_tokens":101656,"cache_creation_input_tokens":662,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":662,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcshgU5pJi2QaPQx9m1nY","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5973d89f-e253-4325-8c14-b32ac5830ad0","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:55:17.422Z","user