{"parentUuid":"1c5a9d68-b035-42e1-944b-a624c3365a25","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshguJct4wrpSVkVqdE3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Tvjs5ix2NkD74sJvehspCK","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\README.md","old_string":"| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. |","new_string":"| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n| `test_quotas_list_delete.py` | `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` integration tests: GET ordering + minimal fields, tenant isolation, empty-list 200, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401; DELETE 204 + row removed, 404 on absent, cross-tenant 404 with the victim row intact, validation 422, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401, `quota.delete`/`quota.forbidden` logging; the two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 rate-limit shape on both verbs; the no-usage-reset / uncapped-events-accepted cross-behavior; the safe-error / fail-closed 500 path on both verbs (AC19); a concurrent-DELETE-of-the-same-row race (exactly one winner); and OpenAPI exposure of both new verbs. |\n| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates/deletes to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. `test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent` (new, quota-admin feature) is the DELETE-specific backstop proof, mirroring the existing read/update cases. |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":490,"cache_read_input_tokens":102318,"output_tokens":1306,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":490},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1306,"cache_read_input_tokens":102318,"cache_creation_input_tokens":490,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":490,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccshgt7SRtC7LoUKEnTeK","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"e4871443-7af7-46cc-ab22-cc28943e2ddd","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:55:29.229Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
