{"parentUuid":"29d93303-0bb3-4053-ad65-59ccdd9efede","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ef7HvwTjQiR2xh4fnpL1CX","type":"tool_result","content":"191\t\n192\t- `api_keys` — the tenant/credential table (migration 0001), extended with a\n193\t  `scope` column (migration 0003: `'ingest'` default, `'admin'` elevated).\n194\t  `secret_hash` is Argon2id; `key_id` is the public split-token lookup\n195\t  handle. `scope='admin'` is a superset scope — an admin key does everything\n196\t  an ingest key does, plus call `PUT /v1/quotas`; a tenant that wants quotas\n197\t  provisions one admin-scoped key and uses it for both.\n198\t- `events` — append-only ingest log (migration 0001). `UNIQUE (api_key_id,\n199\t  idempotency_key)` is the idempotency guarantee; RLS policy\n200\t  `events_tenant_isolation` is the application-scoping backstop."}]},"uuid":"2fb76474-9512-4180-bfff-54e5c195c48b","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:56:18.672Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"29d93303-0bb3-4053-ad65-59ccdd9efede","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
