{"parentUuid":"6928c532-70e5-4773-b0a2-97162487f13a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa8d8d09b1b911247","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcshnASb8Y6TGJzQFwXKd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TGaPWfqMfeUsAP45Ve3tMF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\pr-description.md","content":"# Quota administration — GET /v1/quotas (list) + DELETE /v1/quotas (remove)\n\n## Summary\n\nCompletes the quota-admin CRUD started by the shipped `metric-quotas` feature (`PUT /v1/quotas`).\nAdds two admin-scoped, tenant-isolated surfaces on the same `/v1/quotas` path: `GET /v1/quotas`\nreturns the caller's full, unpaginated, deterministically ordered quota list; `DELETE\n/v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y` removes one cap, returning 204 on success or an explicit 404 if\nno such quota exists in the caller's tenant (not silently idempotent). Both reuse the existing\n`_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency chain, the same anchored `customer_id`/`metric`\nallowlists, `scoped_transaction`, and the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE-RLS policy the shipped\n`PUT` already established — no new table, no new Alembic migration, no new credential, and no\nchange to `POST /v1/events` behavior beyond deletion removing the cap (never the recorded\n`usage_rollup` counters). See `.pipeline/plan.md` for the full design rationale and its STRIDE\nthreat model (also mirrored in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Request flow — `GET`/`DELETE\n/v1/quotas`\" section).\n\n## Changes\n\n- **API layer** (`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`):\n  new `GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` handlers on the existing router; new `QuotaDeleteParams` query-param\n  schema (reuses `QuotaPutRequest`'s `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists, `extra='forbid'`); `DELETE`\n  added to CORS `allow_methods` (inert — empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API).\n- **Service layer** (`src/services/quota_service.py`): new `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` and\n  `delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)`; the latter raises `HTTPException(404)` on no match and\n  logs `quota.delete` INFO on success.\n- **Repository layer** (`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`): new `list_quotas(session, *,\n  api_key_id)` (ordered, tenant-scoped `SELECT`) and `delete_quota(session, *, api_key_id,\n  customer_id, metric)` (parameterized `DELETE ... RETURNING customer_id`, returns whether a row\n  matched).\n- **Security fix included in this diff** (found and fixed by the security stage, not part of the\n  planned feature scope): `.gitignore` was missing a `.terraform/` entry, so ~108 MB of vendored\n  Terraform provider binaries were entering the diff-scoped change set as untracked files. Added\n  `.terraform/` to `.gitignore`; the committable `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` (provider pinning) is\n  deliberately left un-ignored.\n- **Docs**: this stage — `docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`,\n  `src/services/README.md`, `src/repositories/README.md`, `tests/README.md`,\n  `tests/integration/README.md`.\n\n## Decisions & tradeoffs\n\n- **DELETE-not-found → 404, not idempotent-204.** A retried DELETE of an already-removed quota\n  returns 404 on the second call — the brief-sanctioned \"deletes are explicit\" contract, and\n  indistinguishable from a cross-tenant delete attempt (both correctly refuse to act; see BOLA note\n  below).\n- **No synchronization added between DELETE and an in-flight `POST /v1/events`.** Both contend on\n  the same quota-row lock (the DELETE's implicit lock vs. the ingest's `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE OF\n  q`), so PostgreSQL serializes them; whichever commits first determines the outcome for reads that\n  follow. This is the brief-accepted same race `PUT`'s replacement semantics already have — no\n  advisory lock, barrier, or usage reset was added.\n- **GET carries no dedicated audit log.** Plan's Open Question 1, resolved to \"no log\" — a plain\n  read of the caller's own config, mirroring `GET /v1/usage`'s precedent (reads don't emit business\n  events; DELETE, a destructive action, does).\n- **Unpaginated GET list.** Accepted per the brief on the assumption that per-tenant quota counts\n  stay small (bounded by admin `PUT` volume); pagination/filtering is a hard out-of-scope exclusion.\n\n## Testing\n\n**Acceptance criteria: 18 test-covered + 1 delegated to security = 19 total** (source:\n`.pipeline/test-results.json` `criteria_covered.by_id`; delegated = entries with `delegated:\n\"security\"`). AC18 (ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set) is the security stage's\ndeliverable, not a test-suite assertion — confirmed reconciled in `.pipeline/security-report.md`\n(section 6g), not counted as test-covered.\n\n- **Suite result:** 216/217 passed. The 1 failure —\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap`\n  — is a **pre-existing** hard-coded p95 timing assert from the already-merged `usage-export`\n  feature (last touched at `bcf16bb`, not in this branch's diff). It has no `@pytest.mark.perf`\n  marker, so it rides `pipeline-ci.yml`'s unfiltered test job. Re-measured this run at p95 3763ms vs.\n  its 3000ms budget, on a dev machine under concurrent Docker/CPU contention (four unrelated\n  containers running); this is a follow-up for the deployment/human owner, **not part of this\n  diff**.\n- **Coverage:** 88.15% lines, **66.67% branches** (combined; gate is `--cov-fail-under=85` on the\n  line figure, met). New/changed feature modules (`routes/quotas.py`, `schemas/quotas.py`,\n  `quota_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; `quotas_repo.py` sits at 71% branch coverage, attributed\n  in `test-results.json` to a coverage.py partial-branch artifact on multi-line return statements\n  that every call-path test does exercise (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found/not-found) —\n  matching an identical pre-existing pattern on the sibling `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`.\n- **Test-pyramid shape:** `pyramid` (project default), realized as 6 unit (schema validation) + 20\n  integration (endpoint/tenancy/concurrency/RLS-backstop) = 26 new tests this feature, out of 217\n  total in the full suite.\n- **Test quality (advisory — `.pipeline/test-quality.json`):** `quality_ok: false`. Mutation testing\n  (mutmut) **could not run** — it refuses to execute natively on Windows (the tool prints a\n  WSL-required message and exits without mutating anything; `scope: []`, not a silently-shrunk\n  measurement). The CI mutation job exists but is `if: false`-gated pending config; mutation coverage\n  for `quotas_repo.py`/`quota_service.py`/`routes/quotas.py`/`schemas/quotas.py` has genuinely never\n  run anywhere yet — flagged honestly rather than a false \"quality_ok: true\". Adversarial-review\n  notable gaps (all low severity except mutation, which is medium): DELETE's own 429 throttle\n  exhaustion is untested (only GET is driven to 429; DELETE is only proven *not* throttled while\n  under capacity); no wrong-type/repeated-query-param coercion test for DELETE's `customer_id`/\n  `metric`; ordering test doesn't probe a same-collation-adjacent-value case; the GET/DELETE\n  forced-error tests monkeypatch at the service layer, not inside the repository's own `text()`\n  execute call.\n\n## Security\n\nScope: diff against `HEAD` (`ef3fb3f`). **Clean — 0 critical findings**, 2 non-blocking warnings:\n1. `CVE-2025-71176` (pytest 8.3.4, dev/test-only dependency, not in the runtime container) — CVSS\n   ~6.8, below the ≥7.0 deploy-gate floor. Safe version `>= 9.0.3`; not auto-bumped per policy (human\n   decides on `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock`).\n2. Pre-existing, out-of-diff-scope note: the Tier-1 pre-auth throttle keys on `request.client.host`\n   with no proxy-header trust configured, so behind the ALB it would bucket per-node rather than\n   per-real-client. Not introduced by this diff (only CORS `DELETE` touches `middleware.py` here);\n   the effective anti-abuse control for these admin routes is Tier-2 (principal-keyed, proven by\n   AC12).\n\nSTRIDE: 10/10 mechanisms verified present and efficacy-correct, 0 missing, 0 new unmodeled threats\n(`stride_new_threats: 0`). ASVS 5.0.0 reconciled across triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/\nV14/V16, including in-scope L3 V8.2.x (object-level authorization / BOLA), proven by the\ncross-tenant-DELETE→404 test (AC8) plus the adversarial RLS-backstop test that strips the\n`api_key_id` filter entirely and shows FORCE RLS alone still confines the DELETE\n(`test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent`).\n\n## Supply chain\n\n- **Lockfile integrity:** clean — no manifest/lockfile drift in the change set (`lockfile-check`).\n- **SBOM:** a CycloneDX SBOM was generated this run (`.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json`), **65 components**.\n  The deployment gate checks this file exists before allowing a deploy.\n\n## Design review (FE Layer 4)\n\nSkipped — API-only project (`CLAUDE.md`: \"Design source: none\"), no design source (`design-approved`\n/ `design-spec.md`) and no `ui.env`. This is a deliberate non-trigger, not a silent gap: there is no\nUI surface for a visual-fidelity/a11y check to run against.\n\n## DAST (runtime)\n\nAdvisory (`.pipeline/dast-review.json`) — OWASP ZAP passive baseline, `target_reached: true`\n(`http://host.docker.internal:8000`, status 200). Alert tally: 0 high, 3 medium, 4 low, 5\ninformational. `over_budget: []`, `within_budget: true` — no severity band exceeded. This is a\npost-GREEN passive scan outside the security loop, not a pass/fail gate; the pre-merge scanners (see\nSecurity above) and human diff review remain the real teeth. Note: the **gating** DAST layers run in\nCI against staging, not in this local run.\n\n## Threat model\n\nSee `.pipeline/plan.md` `## Threat Model` (STRIDE, scoped to this feature) for the full table and\nMermaid DFD. Highest-severity items and their mitigations:\n- **Spoofing / EoP (function-level), High:** unauthenticated or non-admin caller hits GET/DELETE →\n  reused `_require_admin_and_throttled` (Argon2id auth + `scope=='admin'` gate → 403).\n- **Tampering (SQLi), High:** injection via `customer_id`/`metric` DELETE query params → anchored\n  `constr` allowlist rejects at the 422 boundary; parameterized `text()` bind params only.\n- **Info disclosure (GET response), High:** leaking internal fields or another tenant's caps →\n  minimal `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` + `api_key_id`-scoped SELECT + FORCE RLS.\n- **EoP (IDOR/BOLA), High:** a key deletes another tenant's cap → `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS\n  means a cross-tenant DELETE matches zero rows → 404 (cannot see or remove the row at all); proven\n  by AC8 and the RLS-backstop adversarial test.\n- **Info disclosure (safe-error), Medium:** a forced DB exception on GET/DELETE → the existing\n  `handle_unexpected_error` generic-500 catch-all (no leak) + `scoped_transaction` rollback\n  (fail-closed, no partial DELETE) — new criterion AC19, added during the plan-audit revision pass\n  (see `.pipeline/plan-audit.md`).\n\n## Design-record retention\n\nPlan, acceptance criteria, plan-audit, security report, and run-summary for this feature are\narchived under `docs/decisions/feature/quota-admin/` (per `doc-conventions`; `.pipeline/` is\ngitignored and overwritten every feature).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_read_input_tokens":110626,"output_tokens":5178,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":812},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5178,"cache_read_input_tokens":110626,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":812,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccshn9MrE3kKbLJ3FkPh1","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ec19f42a-4fe1-436b-ae5e-04f7eda03d05","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:57:20.897Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
